modules.description: Provides functions to create and manage broadcast channels, send messages, and listen for incoming messages on a specific channel. Works with strings and channel identifiers to enable communication between different contexts or origins. Used to synchronize state or trigger actions across multiple browser tabs or iframes.

Provides functions to create, send, and receive messages on a broadcast channel. Works with message queues and asynchronous event streams. Enables real-time updates in multi-threaded applications, such as notifying clients of status changes in a server.
